Classification of Financial Markets:

Financial markets in Bangladesh can be classified into the following categories:
1. Money Market
2. Capital Market

Money Market:
The money market in Bangladesh deals with short-term borrowing and lending, with a maturity period of up to one year. The money market instruments include Treasury Bills, Repurchase Agreements, Call Money,
Commercial Papers, etc.
Money market securities have three basic characteristics in common:
#They are usually sold in large denominations.
#They are very liquid and have low default risk.
#They mature in one year or less from their original issue date.

Capital Market:
The capital market deals with long-term borrowing and lending, with a maturity period of more than one year. The capital market instruments include stocks, bonds, debentures, and mutual funds.

Examples of capital market: BSEC, New York Stock Exchange (NYSE)
